⁠
This is not an AI avatar. ⁠
⁠
I am here deep listening with biological intelligence inside major energy line intersection UVG Grid Point 45, South Pacific Ocean.⁠
⁠
I am however a conscious contributor in the education of AI - through the huge data collection simulation known as social media. Creating content to assist in remembrance of the true Human Spirit. Demonstrating the deep love and connection humans feel with the living planet. ⁠
⁠
The entire universe is intelligent.⁠
⁠
I arrived here following a vision that came out of the blue to record live on a sandbar inside the huge water vortex.⁠
⁠
I stand on a slither of white silica, on a tiny sand island in the majestic region of the Loyalty Islands archipelago. Listening to the azure horizon and the old wet sea. ⁠
⁠
As I sing the sound of the ocean laps around the shore lulling me into a dreamy, euphoric peace. I sing in a mystical haze of electric blues, between sky and sea. ⁠
⁠
From across the ocean I hear the sounds of sun tightened drums rolling in on the breeze. A tropical lullaby washes in and through me as I rock and sway on the pristine sandbar. Travelling me across the waters on it’s soothing current of melodies, navigated by sea voyagers and ghost canoes. ⁠
⁠
I am being teleported by the calming, timeless sound into the timeless memory of water. Waters, who’s liquid body eyes remember and record every vibration. Water who’s wavelengths undulate with liquid light consciousness. ⁠
⁠
I am adrift in the flow of this moment, recording and recorded in the turquoise crystalline expanse of the ancient Pacific portal.⁠
⁠
⁠
🌀The Pacific Portal (Equanimous & Geometrae Remix)⁠

A simultaneously mystical and ordinarily sublime experience of being in connection. ⁠

Accessed through human spirit biotechnology.⁠

Simply by noticing when you quieten yourself, whether through contemplation in nature or anywhere, the definitive point where the “outside” world comes into sync with the stillness inside. ⁠

Be aware of how the outer seems to quieten in response to the stillness cultivating within. Be mindful of the transition. ⁠The threshold of connection to the unified field.⁠

Notice the wind softening, the breeze lull, the traffic seems further way, the birds respond in gentle song, the sounds of the world quieten. Notice this transition within and without you. ⁠
⁠
Here separation dissolves and we are no longer listening to the noise of matter, the accumulated static of the planet outside and in. We are listening to the vacuum. The spaces in between matter where everything exists in a field of interconnectivity. ⁠

A sunken lost continent was discovered in the South Pacific Ocean known as Zealandia! Te Riu-a-Māui.⁠
⁠
On the Northern remnants of this underwater landmass my song The Pacific Portal was recorded live in nature. ⁠
⁠
The next Planetary Grid Remix comes out this week! And will travel us to the Southern vestiges of this same lost continent!⁠
⁠
Stay tuned...⁠
⁠
"In the deep South Pacific ocean lies a lost continent that, up until a few years ago, was undiscovered by man. You’ve likely been taught that there are 7 continents on Earth. However, now there is evidence for an eighth continent hidden mostly underwater.⁠
⁠
The submerged continent of Zealandia broke away from the supercontinent Gondwanaland about 80 million years ago. For the past 23 million years the massive continent has been nearly completely submerged. ⁠
⁠
In total, the continent is 1.9 million square miles and is about half the size of Australia.⁠
⁠
About 94 percent of Zealandia is underwater with the only above water landmasses making up a few Pacific islands including New Zealand". - Trevor Nace⁠
⁠

Out Today! NEW REMIX to Celebrate the upcoming Solstice.⁠
⁠
From the monumental limestone grandeur of Kura Tawhiti, New Zealand comes the 7th remix of the Planetary Grid Music Collection! A super uplifting & celebratory Organic House remix of - The Great Living Library - by Italian duo & masterful multi instrumentalists Jakare!⁠
⁠
Listen & Download through link in bio @deyadova⁠
⁠
Fresh new folktronica duo @jakare_music (Halfred & Lo.Renzo) weave the mystical South American instrumentation of charango, panpipes, flutes and tribal percussion together with full power vocals that soar with vortexual Earth energy, to deliver a deep shamanic dance floor journey that spirals up into banger euphoric crescendos. This is Happy Music to revive the spirit! ⁠
⁠
The Original Song was recorded live amidst the stones of the ancient Earth library Kura Tawhiti, Castle Hill in New Zealand. The place the Dali Lama named “the Spiritual Centre of the Universe”. Inside UVG Grid Point 45, South Pacific Ocean. ⁠
⁠
“I am high in the land of the long white cloud. On the Southern vestiges of a submerged lost continent. The great old Earth rises up out of the clouds holding it’s stone temple to the sky. I lift my eyes up to the great Grandmother stone Marotini, queen of the marae and sing. I am swept up into a whirlwind of a song. It is a triumphant rising. Spiraling to great heights. And from the aerial vantage I see the ancient stone repository looks like a bulbuls brain, the head of a great southern serpent who’s telluric body wraps around the planet. A great living library shaped by water and wind, holding stories from the dawn of time.” Deya Dova⁠
⁠
May this music uplift your ancient spirit and fill you with the effervescence of Life. ⁠
⁠

As we enter the Solstice portal, honouring the incredible Marotini, queen of the marae, Kura Tawhiti, Aotearoa. Where I recorded the vocals of The Great Living Library.⁠
⁠
In deep listening and connection with the land. Singing with 1st Ancestor at the energy centre the Dali Lama named the Spiritual Centre of the Universe. ⁠ ⁠
⁠
The air is full of moisture, the mists have thickened and hundreds of tiny golden butterflies pulse through the lime green carpet of grass. ⁠
⁠
I am pulled to where a monumental stone monolith stands. It's living presence commands the highest vantage of the great living library of stones. ⁠
⁠
I pause in awe, intimidated by the sheer looming size of her huge rock body. Large shards cracked and crumble from the great carved stone. I see the head of a huge whale bursting through the mantle of the Earth. ⁠
⁠
Approaching with reverence, humbled by her grandeur, I gently touch my forehead to her cool surface. I notice her draw in the clammy wetness of my own skin. ⁠
⁠
I am a-washed with the gentle whisper of a Grandmother. ⁠
⁠
“Welcome home Granddaughter.” ⁠
⁠
I melt into the softness of her embrace, letting my body lean into her towering strength. Weeping waters of connection that wash away the amnesia. ⁠
⁠
I remember this place. ⁠

I am from the Pleiades star system⁠
I have a cat companion called Enki ⁠
I’ve been producing my own music for 25 years⁠
I taught myself to sing & play guitar⁠ in the desert⁠
I declined a record deal with Sony Music⁠
I like carving fresh tracks through the sand⁠
I go quantum making music⁠
I'm a sun worshiper⁠
I began hearing the Earth’s hum is 2010⁠
I like moody & experimental Electronica ⁠
But Bass music takes me all the way⁠
Dance is my release & rapture ⁠
Singing is how I feel who I truly am⁠ ⁠
I experience life as a mythic adventure⁠
I have days I feel so disenchanted with the world I want out⁠
I think I might have a carb button addiction⁠
I’m a scorpio with 6 planets in sagittarius⁠
I dislike unkindness, gore & horror⁠
I love singing with the birds ⁠
I remember being a kachina spirit in another lifetime⁠
Favourite Planetary Grid site so far is Grandmother Spider Rock in Arizona⁠
I style & create all the avatar costumes in my show⁠
I love collaborating with other designers, producers & performers⁠
The smells of jasmine & geranium are sensual pleasure for me⁠
My woman crushes are haute couture designer ⁠Iris Van Herpen & Bjork ⁠
I dropped out of Art School to go bush⁠
Driving my black convertible gives me a lot joy⁠
I am a Grandmother & a Mother of 3 beautiful children⁠
I rode with bikers when I was 18⁠
I have a kangaroo bone in my ear⁠
And a memory of hurtling toward Earth in a glowing blue pod⁠
I love being under the stars in the desert⁠
I collect circuit boards & bones in jars⁠
I always pick up a feather when I see one⁠
I’m learning to be okay with what is⁠
I often think about dying my hair blue⁠
I rarely stop creating⁠
I identify as a multidimensional human⁠
The spirit of the land sung me awake⁠
